headline: Natural gas flares sparked 2 wildfires in North Dakota, state agency says
summary: Natural gas flares at oil wells sparked two North Dakota wildfires earlier this fall, according to reports from the North Dakota Fire Marshal's Office.  Investigators concluded that flares combined with high winds and extremely dry weather and started a wildfire near the town of Keene and another near New Town, the Bismarck Tribune reported Thursday.  Officials with ConocoPhillips and Hess Corp., which operate the oil wells, say they are still reviewing the reports.

headline: APA Q3 Earnings Miss Even as Callon Buyout Drives Production
summary: APA bought back 102,305 shares at $29.32 apiece during the third quarter. The company also shelled out $92 million in dividend payments.
